# Augment Guidelines for secure_qr_scanner Website

## Project Overview
This is the marketing website for the secure_qr_scanner Flutter app. Built with SolidStart (SolidJS SSR) and TailwindCSS v4.

## Key Technologies
- **Framework**: SolidStart (SolidJS with SSR)
- **Styling**: TailwindCSS v4
- **Language**: TypeScript
- **Package Manager**: pnpm

## Design System
- **Theme**: Purple gradient matching the Flutter app
- **Colors**: 
  - Primary: #8B5CF6 (violet-500)
  - Secondary: #D946EF (fuchsia-500)
  - Accent: #7C3AED (violet-600)
- **Font**: Inter (system-ui fallback)
- **Dark Mode**: Respects `prefers-color-scheme: dark`

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript for all components
- Follow SolidJS reactive patterns (createSignal, createEffect)
- Use TailwindCSS utility classes for styling
- Keep components small and focused
- Prefer composition over inheritance

## File Organization
```
website/
├── src/
│   ├── routes/          # Page components (file-based routing)
│   ├── components/      # Reusable UI components
│   ├── styles/          # Global styles (app.css)
│   └── app.tsx          # Root component
├── public/              # Static assets
└── app.config.ts        # SolidStart configuration
```

## Routing
- SolidStart uses file-based routing
- `src/routes/index.tsx` → `/` (home page)
- `src/routes/privacy.tsx` → `/privacy` (privacy policy)
- `src/routes/terms.tsx` → `/terms` (terms of service)

## SEO Requirements
- Add proper `<Title>` and `<Meta>` tags to all pages
- Use semantic HTML (header, main, footer, nav, article)
- Implement proper heading hierarchy (h1 → h2 → h3)
- Add Open Graph tags for social sharing
- Optimize images with proper alt text

## Performance
- Leverage SSR for fast initial page loads
- Minimize JavaScript bundle size
- Optimize images (WebP format when possible)
- Use lazy loading for below-the-fold content
- Ensure fast Time to First Byte (TTFB)

## Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Ensure proper color contrast (WCAG 2.1 AA)
- Add ARIA labels where needed
- Support keyboard navigation
- Test with screen readers

## Content Pages Required
1. **Home/Landing Page** - App overview and features
2. **Privacy Policy** - Required for Google Play publishing
3. **Terms of Service** - Legal terms and conditions

## Common Patterns

### Page Template
```tsx
import { Title, Meta } from '@solidjs/meta';

export default function PageName() {
  return (
    <>
      <Title>Page Title - QR Scanner</Title>
      <Meta name="description" content="Page description" />
      
      <main class="min-h-screen">
        {/* Page content */}
      </main>
    </>
  );
}
```

### Gradient Background
```tsx
<div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-[#8B5CF6] via-[#D946EF] to-[#7C3AED]">
  {/* Content */}
</div>
```

### Glassmorphism Effect
```tsx
<div class="backdrop-blur-lg bg-white/10 border border-white/20 rounded-2xl">
  {/* Content */}
</div>
```

## Testing Checklist
- [ ] TypeScript compiles without errors
- [ ] Pages render correctly in light and dark modes
- [ ] Responsive design works on mobile/tablet/desktop
- [ ] SSR hydration works without errors
- [ ] SEO meta tags are present and correct
- [ ] Accessibility: keyboard navigation works
- [ ] Accessibility: screen reader friendly
- [ ] Performance: fast page loads

## Development Workflow
1. Create/modify components in `src/components/`
2. Create/modify pages in `src/routes/`
3. Test locally with `pnpm dev`
4. Run type checking with `pnpm typecheck`
5. Build for production with `pnpm build`
6. Test production build with `pnpm start`

## Notes
- This website is separate from the Flutter app but shares the same design language
- The website is primarily for Google Play requirements (privacy policy) and marketing
- Keep the website lightweight and fast-loading
- Ensure all content is mobile-friendly
